# Dragon Disciple
(Adapted from Pathfinder's 1e)

A dragon disciple is a character who has willingly embraced his draconic heritage and, through the power of magic, is able to harness his draconic bloodline to enhance his own abilities. (Copilot generated comment)

**Hit Die**: d12.

### Requirements

To qualify to become a dragon disciple, a character must fulfill all the following criteria.

**Race**: Any non-dragon.

**Skills**: Arcana.

**Languages**: Draconic.

**Spellcasting**: Ability to cast 1st-level arcane spells. If the character has sorcerer levels, he must have the draconic bloodline. If the character gains levels of sorcerer after taking this class, he must take the draconic bloodline.


